C TC11
(* JMM causality test case 11 (Pugh 2004). Same data-dependency cycle as TC02 but the *)
(* shared locations are INITIALISED to 1. Reading 1 is now justified by the initial    *)
(* write, not by the cycle, so the outcome is NOT thin-air. JMM DECISION: ALLOWED.     *)
(* Encoded with copy-form stores: the initial write of value 1 lets both reads wire to *)
(* it faithfully, and the dependency cycle no longer needs to justify the value.       *)
{ x=1; y=1; }
P0(int *x, int *y) { r0 = READ_ONCE(*y); WRITE_ONCE(*x, r0); }
P1(int *x, int *y) { r0 = READ_ONCE(*x); WRITE_ONCE(*y, r0); }
exists (0:r0=1 /\ 1:r0=1)
